[
    {
        "text": "Welcome to the University of Nottingham and the Department of Theology and Religious Studies.",
        "startTime": 1404,
        "endTime": 5170,
        "slowStartTime": 2256,
        "slowEndTime": 7980
    },
    {
        "text": "Welcome to another in the series \"Sacred Calendars\",...",
        "startTime": 6125,
        "endTime": 9317,
        "slowStartTime": 9337,
        "slowEndTime": 14201
    },
    {
        "text": "...where we look at festivals and feasts in different religious traditions.",
        "startTime": 9867,
        "endTime": 13702,
        "slowStartTime": 14951,
        "slowEndTime": 20778
    },
    {
        "text": "With me today, we have Mr. Shujahat Aslam, who is an imam here in Nottingham,...",
        "startTime": 14847,
        "endTime": 20492,
        "slowStartTime": 22420,
        "slowEndTime": 30963
    },
    {
        "text": "...who occasionally also gives the Friday sermon at the University of Nottingham's mosque.",
        "startTime": 21251,
        "endTime": 26216,
        "slowStartTime": 32027,
        "slowEndTime": 39549
    },
    {
        "text": "Shujahat, welcome.",
        "startTime": 26770,
        "endTime": 27903,
        "slowStartTime": 40305,
        "slowEndTime": 42080
    },
    {
        "text": "Thank you.",
        "startTime": 28138,
        "endTime": 28444,
        "slowStartTime": 42357,
        "slowEndTime": 42891
    },
    {
        "text": "Today we'll be talking with you about Eid al-Fitr.",
        "startTime": 29351,
        "endTime": 32573,
        "slowStartTime": 44176,
        "slowEndTime": 49084
    },
    {
        "text": "First of all, can you tell us a little bit about what Eid al-Fitr is?",
        "startTime": 33558,
        "endTime": 37473,
        "slowStartTime": 50487,
        "slowEndTime": 56435
    },
    {
        "text": "Sure.",
        "startTime": 37646,
        "endTime": 37861,
        "slowStartTime": 56619,
        "slowEndTime": 57016
    },
    {
        "text": "The word \"eid\" in Arabic means celebration or festivity.",
        "startTime": 38517,
        "endTime": 41251,
        "slowStartTime": 57925,
        "slowEndTime": 62102
    },
    {
        "text": "So Eid al-Fitr is the first festivity in the Islamic calendar.",
        "startTime": 41769,
        "endTime": 45154,
        "slowStartTime": 62804,
        "slowEndTime": 67956
    },
    {
        "text": "It's linked to the blessed month of Ramadan.",
        "startTime": 46267,
        "endTime": 48041,
        "slowStartTime": 69550,
        "slowEndTime": 72286
    },
    {
        "text": "Ramadan is a month in which Muslims the world over fast.",
        "startTime": 48326,
        "endTime": 50996,
        "slowStartTime": 72639,
        "slowEndTime": 76719
    },
    {
        "text": "That means that they don't have anything to eat or drink throughout daylight hours.",
        "startTime": 51441,
        "endTime": 54327,
        "slowStartTime": 77311,
        "slowEndTime": 81716
    },
    {
        "text": "Fasting in the month of Ramadan lasts for 29 or 30 days.",
        "startTime": 54993,
        "endTime": 57922,
        "slowStartTime": 82639,
        "slowEndTime": 87108
    },
    {
        "text": "After 29 days, Muslims go out to seek if it's the day of Eid al-Fitr or not.",
        "startTime": 58583,
        "endTime": 62531,
        "slowStartTime": 88025,
        "slowEndTime": 94022
    },
    {
        "text": "This is determined by whether the new moon is sighted,....",
        "startTime": 63112,
        "endTime": 65567,
        "slowStartTime": 94818,
        "slowEndTime": 98576
    },
    {
        "text": "...which shows that the Islamic month of Ramadan has finished.",
        "startTime": 66030,
        "endTime": 68411,
        "slowStartTime": 99195,
        "slowEndTime": 102842
    },
    {
        "text": "If the new moon is sighted, it means that it's the day of Eid,...",
        "startTime": 69725,
        "endTime": 71981,
        "slowStartTime": 104738,
        "slowEndTime": 108197
    },
    {
        "text": "...so all the fasting ends on that day.",
        "startTime": 72048,
        "endTime": 73773,
        "slowStartTime": 108222,
        "slowEndTime": 110885
    },
    {
        "text": "And in the Islamic calendar, the night precedes the day.",
        "startTime": 74513,
        "endTime": 76977,
        "slowStartTime": 111919,
        "slowEndTime": 115690
    },
    {
        "text": "So therefore first of all, you have the night of the day of Eid al-Fitr, followed by the day.",
        "startTime": 77318,
        "endTime": 81677,
        "slowStartTime": 116127,
        "slowEndTime": 122741
    },
    {
        "text": "So you're looking for the moon when?",
        "startTime": 82207,
        "endTime": 83867,
        "slowStartTime": 123461,
        "slowEndTime": 126026
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah.",
        "startTime": 84140,
        "endTime": 84371,
        "slowStartTime": 126360,
        "slowEndTime": 126781
    },
    {
        "text": "Tonight?",
        "startTime": 84559,
        "endTime": 84907,
        "slowStartTime": 126988,
        "slowEndTime": 127585
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, that's right, so in the evening.",
        "startTime": 85253,
        "endTime": 86618,
        "slowStartTime": 128029,
        "slowEndTime": 130152
    },
    {
        "text": "So once the 29th fast is finished, you open your fast,...",
        "startTime": 86703,
        "endTime": 89338,
        "slowStartTime": 130204,
        "slowEndTime": 134232
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.",
        "startTime": 89536,
        "endTime": 89792,
        "slowStartTime": 134454,
        "slowEndTime": 134913
    },
    {
        "text": "...so this is kind of evening time, therefore people will go out and see if the moon is sighted.",
        "startTime": 90428,
        "endTime": 94108,
        "slowStartTime": 135792,
        "slowEndTime": 141387
    },
    {
        "text": "If there's a new moon there, it means that the month of Ramadan has finished...",
        "startTime": 94240,
        "endTime": 97057,
        "slowStartTime": 141510,
        "slowEndTime": 145811
    },
    {
        "text": "...and the new month has started, therefore this indicates that's the beginning of Eid al-Fitr.",
        "startTime": 97156,
        "endTime": 101283,
        "slowStartTime": 145884,
        "slowEndTime": 152149
    },
    {
        "text": "So you go through the night which is pretty much the same as previous nights,...",
        "startTime": 102435,
        "endTime": 105224,
        "slowStartTime": 153803,
        "slowEndTime": 158061
    },
    {
        "text": "...except that you don't pray the kind of night prayer, the tarawih prayer.",
        "startTime": 105291,
        "endTime": 108732,
        "slowStartTime": 158086,
        "slowEndTime": 163323
    },
    {
        "text": "But really, Eid starts in the morning.",
        "startTime": 109440,
        "endTime": 110943,
        "slowStartTime": 164310,
        "slowEndTime": 166640
    },
    {
        "text": "And the first and most important thing as a kind of religious ritual or festival...",
        "startTime": 111667,
        "endTime": 115465,
        "slowStartTime": 167650,
        "slowEndTime": 173422
    },
    {
        "text": "...that you have to do is to be charitable on the day of Eid.",
        "startTime": 115527,
        "endTime": 118382,
        "slowStartTime": 173440,
        "slowEndTime": 177798
    },
    {
        "text": "So you have to pay a certain amount of money called \"Zakat al-Fitr\".",
        "startTime": 118937,
        "endTime": 122543,
        "slowStartTime": 178556,
        "slowEndTime": 184040
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.",
        "startTime": 122759,
        "endTime": 123045,
        "slowStartTime": 184289,
        "slowEndTime": 184792
    },
    {
        "text": "This is given generally in foodstuff, there's kind of grain or wheat or barley,...",
        "startTime": 123200,
        "endTime": 127692,
        "slowStartTime": 184950,
        "slowEndTime": 191763
    },
    {
        "text": "...the equivalent of about five pounds worth of foodstuff is given to the poor.",
        "startTime": 128473,
        "endTime": 131619,
        "slowStartTime": 192860,
        "slowEndTime": 197653
    },
    {
        "text": "So in an Islamic country, you'd go before the time of the Eid prayer,...",
        "startTime": 132805,
        "endTime": 136001,
        "slowStartTime": 199357,
        "slowEndTime": 204227
    },
    {
        "text": "...and the poor people would be gathered and you'd give that foodstuffs to them.",
        "startTime": 136355,
        "endTime": 139305,
        "slowStartTime": 204682,
        "slowEndTime": 209183
    },
    {
        "text": "Clearly in the UK, it's quite not easy to do that.",
        "startTime": 139690,
        "endTime": 142199,
        "slowStartTime": 209685,
        "slowEndTime": 213524
    },
    {
        "text": "So generally what Muslims would do during the month of Ramadan,...",
        "startTime": 142535,
        "endTime": 145020,
        "slowStartTime": 213952,
        "slowEndTime": 217755
    },
    {
        "text": "...they would give the money to an Islamic charity,...",
        "startTime": 145311,
        "endTime": 147073,
        "slowStartTime": 218117,
        "slowEndTime": 220834
    },
    {
        "text": "...where they arrange to spend that money on their behalf to the poor wherever they may be.",
        "startTime": 147563,
        "endTime": 151300,
        "slowStartTime": 221494,
        "slowEndTime": 227175
    },
    {
        "text": "On the morning of the Eid?",
        "startTime": 151657,
        "endTime": 152810,
        "slowStartTime": 227636,
        "slowEndTime": 229440
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, generally it should be done before the Eid Salah.",
        "startTime": 152926,
        "endTime": 155465,
        "slowStartTime": 229539,
        "slowEndTime": 233422
    },
    {
        "text": "So generally, they try and do it as soon as possible, up to the time of the Eid Salah.",
        "startTime": 155703,
        "endTime": 159598,
        "slowStartTime": 233705,
        "slowEndTime": 239622
    },
    {
        "text": "The benefit of this is the poor can participate in Eid along with the rest of society as well.",
        "startTime": 160601,
        "endTime": 165217,
        "slowStartTime": 241052,
        "slowEndTime": 248050
    }
]